1
00:00:00,918 --> 00:00:03,337
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

2
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:13,514
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

3
00:00:13,514 --> 00:00:15,474
Come in.

4
00:00:22,940 --> 00:00:25,233
ARCHER: GOOD MORNING.

5
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,485
CAPTAIN.

6
00:00:26,485 --> 00:00:27,736
SLEEP WELL?

7
00:00:27,736 --> 00:00:29,905
WELL ENOUGH.

8
00:00:29,905 --> 00:00:31,573
I WASN'T SURE WHAT
YOU WANTED FOR BREAKFAST,

9
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,826
SO I TOOK THE LIBERTY
OF HAVING CHEF PREPARE

10
00:00:33,826 --> 00:00:35,870
HIS FAMOUS EGGS BENEDICT.

11
00:00:35,870 --> 00:00:38,288
OH. THAT'LL BE FINE, SIR.

12
00:00:38,288 --> 00:00:40,123
ARCHER: AH.

13
00:00:40,123 --> 00:00:42,710
YOU PLAN TO EAT STANDING UP?

14
00:00:42,710 --> 00:00:44,753
[ CHUCKLES ]

15
00:00:48,423 --> 00:00:50,091
[ SIGHS ]

16
00:00:51,927 --> 00:00:55,263
THIS ISN'T A VISIT TO THE
PRINCIPAL'S OFFICE, MALCOLM.

17
00:00:55,263 --> 00:00:57,265
AT EASE.

18
00:00:57,265 --> 00:00:59,226
OH, THANK YOU, SIR.

19
00:00:59,226 --> 00:01:00,936
I JUST WASN'T SURE

20
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:04,398
WHETHER YOU CALLED ME HERE
TO DISCUSS SOMETHING.

21
00:01:04,398 --> 00:01:06,358
NO. NO BUSINESS.

22
00:01:06,358 --> 00:01:08,569
I JUST WANTED TO HAVE
A LONG-OVERDUE MEAL

23
00:01:08,569 --> 00:01:10,320
WITH MY ARMORY OFFICER.

24
00:01:11,989 --> 00:01:13,657
AH.

25
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:17,244
I HEARD THAT ENGLAND MADE IT

26
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:19,663
TO THE FINALS
IN THE WORLD CUP.

27
00:01:19,663 --> 00:01:21,790
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

28
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:24,418
THE WORLD CUP?

29
00:01:24,418 --> 00:01:25,920
SOCCER?

30
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,629
OH.

31
00:01:27,629 --> 00:01:30,340
I'M AFRAID I DON'T
MUCH FOLLOW FOOTBALL, SIR.

32
00:01:30,340 --> 00:01:34,469
ANY...SPORTS YOU DO FOLLOW?

33
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:37,598
NO. NOT PARTICULARLY.

34
00:01:40,935 --> 00:01:42,143
THANKS.

35
00:01:42,143 --> 00:01:44,229
YOU'RE WELCOME, SIR.

36
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:47,399
[ SIGHS ]

37
00:01:47,399 --> 00:01:49,985
I'VE BEEN WORKING ON
THE DUTY ROSTER, SIR.

38
00:01:49,985 --> 00:01:51,987
WE ONLY HAVE
TWO CREWMEN ASSIGNED

39
00:01:51,987 --> 00:01:53,405
TO THE ARMORY FULL-TIME.

40
00:01:53,405 --> 00:01:55,365
IF WE ADDED A THIRD,

41
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:58,786
ENSIGN TANNER WOULD BE FREE
TO BEGIN THOSE UPGRADES

42
00:01:58,786 --> 00:02:01,371
TO THOSE TORPEDO LAUNCHERS
I TOLD YOU ABOUT.

43
00:02:01,371 --> 00:02:03,415
DIDN'T YOUR MOTHER
EVER TELL YOU

44
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:05,626
NOT TO BRING
YOUR HOMEWORK TO THE TABLE?

45
00:02:05,626 --> 00:02:07,753
SIR?

46
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:14,843
-THIS LOOKS FINE.
-AH.

47
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:16,887
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

48
00:02:19,765 --> 00:02:21,516
ARCHER.

49
00:02:21,516 --> 00:02:24,227
T'Pol: I'm sorry to interrupt,
Captain, but we've detected

50
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:26,897
an uncharted system
along our present course.

51
00:02:26,897 --> 00:02:29,232
One of the planets
is Minshara-class.

52
00:02:29,232 --> 00:02:32,360
TAKE US OUT OF WARP.
I'M ON MY WAY.

53
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:39,618
LOOKS LIKE WE'LL HAVE
TO RESCHEDULE.

54
00:02:39,618 --> 00:02:41,369
WHENEVER IT'S CONVENIENT.

55
00:02:45,791 --> 00:02:47,459
AFTER YOU, SIR.

56
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:01,306
ANYBODY HOME?

57
00:03:01,306 --> 00:03:03,308
IT'S UNINHABITED.

58
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:05,811
WHAT ABOUT GEOGRAPHICAL
FEATURES? ANYTHING INTERESTING?

59
00:03:05,811 --> 00:03:07,688
T'POL: THERE'S A CHAIN
OF VOLCANOES

60
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:09,439
THAT SPANS
AN ENTIRE HEMISPHERE.

61
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:10,983
WELL, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT ANYONE ELSE,

62
00:03:10,983 --> 00:03:12,776
BUT I COULD USE SOME FRESH AIR.

63
00:03:12,776 --> 00:03:14,820
PUT US IN A STANDARD ORBIT.

64
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:16,404
AYE, SIR.

65
00:03:16,404 --> 00:03:18,573
FIND A VOLCANO
WITH A GENTLE SLOPE,

66
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:21,493
PREFERABLY ONE
THAT'S NOT ERUPTING.

67
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:23,912
PREP A SHUTTLEPOD, TRAVIS.

68
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:26,123
WE'LL TAKE SHIFTS DOWN TO --

69
00:03:26,123 --> 00:03:27,499
[ EXPLOSION ]

70
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:43,264
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

71
00:03:43,264 --> 00:03:46,476
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

72
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:50,397
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

73
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:53,901
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

74
00:03:53,901 --> 00:03:58,405
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

75
00:03:58,405 --> 00:04:01,783
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

76
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:05,787
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

77
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:08,916
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

78
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,752
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

79
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:14,171
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

80
00:04:14,171 --> 00:04:17,632
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

81
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:22,262
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

82
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:24,890
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

83
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:29,811
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

84
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:33,107
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

85
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:38,070
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

86
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:39,780
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

87
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:42,365
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

88
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:45,619
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

89
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:50,665
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

90
00:05:01,885 --> 00:05:03,344
ARCHER: REPORT!

91
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:04,846
IT WAS A THERMOKINETIC EXPLOSION

92
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:07,891
ON THE OUTER HULL,
PORT-FORWARD QUARTER.

93
00:05:07,891 --> 00:05:11,686
BREACHES ON "C" DECK, "D" DECK.

94
00:05:11,686 --> 00:05:14,689
BRIDGE TO SICK BAY.
WE NEED MEDICAL ASSISTANCE.

95
00:05:14,689 --> 00:05:16,817
-Acknowledged.
-EMERGENCY BULKHEADS?

96
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:18,068
THEY'RE IN PLACE,

97
00:05:18,068 --> 00:05:19,653
BUT EIGHT SUBSECTIONS
HAVE DECOMPRESSED.

98
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:22,948
-WAS ANYBODY IN THEM?
-I CAN'T TELL, SIR, NOT YET.

99
00:05:22,948 --> 00:05:25,033
FIND OUT WHAT HAPPENED.

100
00:05:28,996 --> 00:05:30,914
MALCOLM!

101
00:05:30,914 --> 00:05:32,916
I'D GIVE YOU AN ANSWER
IF I COULD, SIR.

102
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:35,335
THE SENSOR LOGS
AREN'T SHOWING ANYTHING.

103
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,671
ALL SYSTEMS WERE
FUNCTIONING NORMALLY.

104
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:38,922
ARCHER TO ENGINEERING.

105
00:05:38,922 --> 00:05:40,423
CAPTAIN, WHAT'S GOING ON?

106
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,009
I was hoping you could tell me.

107
00:05:42,009 --> 00:05:44,803
WE'VE GOT PLASMA FIRES,
AN OVERLOAD IN THE E.P.S. GRID,

108
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:47,514
BUT WHATEVER CAUSED THAT
EXPLOSION, I DON'T HAVE A CLUE.

109
00:05:47,514 --> 00:05:49,099
Weapons fire? An asteroid?

110
00:05:49,099 --> 00:05:52,186
NOTHING ON OUR SENSORS.
HOW ARE YOUR PEOPLE?

111
00:05:52,186 --> 00:05:54,021
TUCKER: A FEW BUMPS AND BRUISES,
BUT WE'RE ALL RIGHT.

112
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:56,773
Keep me posted. Archer out.

113
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:58,233
ANY CASUALTY REPORTS?

114
00:05:58,233 --> 00:05:59,860
FIGURES ARE COMING IN, SIR.

115
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:02,361
17 SO FAR, INCLUDING HOSHI.

116
00:06:02,361 --> 00:06:04,114
NO FATALITIES.

117
00:06:04,114 --> 00:06:05,615
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

118
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:14,624
GET THIS MAN INTO
THE IMAGING CHAMBER.

119
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:21,506
WHAT'S HAPPENING?
ARE WE UNDER ATTACK?

120
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:23,633
-I DON'T KNOW.
-DOCTOR!

121
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:29,430
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
YOU'RE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

122
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:32,767
EASY. EASY.

123
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,811
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]
CAPTAIN.

124
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:36,813
SOMETHING JUST STRUCK THE SHIP.

125
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,815
STARBOARD SIDE.

126
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:40,441
UPPER-AFT QUADRANT.

127
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:42,485
CAN YOU GET A VISUAL?

128
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:51,286
THERE.

129
00:06:51,286 --> 00:06:53,038
JUST BEHIND
THE SECONDARY PLASMA VENT.

130
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:55,374
YOU SEE IT?

131
00:06:56,917 --> 00:06:59,086
TRAVIS: SOME KIND
OF CLOAKED SHIP?

132
00:06:59,086 --> 00:07:01,629
IT'S TOO SMALL.

133
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:04,799
T'POL: I'M NOT READING
ANY BIO-SIGNS.

134
00:07:07,886 --> 00:07:10,931
REED: IT'S ARMED
WITH TRICOBALT EXPLOSIVES.

135
00:07:10,931 --> 00:07:12,391
I THINK IT'S A MINE.

136
00:07:12,391 --> 00:07:13,975
AND JUDGING BY THE FIREPOWER,

137
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:16,603
SOMETHING SIMILAR
DAMAGED OUR SHIP.

138
00:07:16,603 --> 00:07:18,688
CAN YOU TELL
IF IT'S ACTIVE?

139
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:20,899
NO REASON TO BELIEVE IT'S NOT.

140
00:07:20,899 --> 00:07:24,319
T'POL: CAPTAIN, IT'S LODGED
NEAR IMPULSE REACTOR 2.

141
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:27,989
AN EXPLOSION ANYWHERE NEAR THERE
COULD DISABLE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

142
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:30,533
WHAT IF WE POLARIZED
THE ADJACENT HULL PLATING?

143
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:32,619
WE DON'T KNOW
HOW IT'S TRIGGERED.

144
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:35,289
SOMEBODY HAS TO GO OUT THERE
AND DEFUSE IT,

145
00:07:35,289 --> 00:07:36,539
AND IT SHOULD BE ME.

146
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,417
I HAVE THE ORDNANCE TRAINING.

147
00:07:53,098 --> 00:07:54,641
ARCHER: I'VE NEVER HEARD OF

148
00:07:54,641 --> 00:07:57,018
A MINEFIELD
WITH JUST TWO MINES.

149
00:07:57,018 --> 00:07:58,519
ARE THE QUANTUM BEACONS

150
00:07:58,519 --> 00:08:01,189
STILL MOUNTED
ON THE GRAPPLER ARM?

151
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:02,816
I BELIEVE SO.

152
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:04,818
LOWER THEM INTO POSITION,

153
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:06,861
THEN MODIFY THE VIEWSCREEN.

154
00:08:17,164 --> 00:08:18,457
ACTIVATE THE BEACON.

155
00:08:22,169 --> 00:08:25,922
THEY WERE DESIGNED TO PENETRATE
SULIBAN CLOAKING DEVICES.

156
00:08:25,922 --> 00:08:28,258
I'LL TRY SHIFTING
THE PHASE VARIANCE.

157
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:08,589
LIEUTENANT REED TO THE BRIDGE.

158
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:11,259
I'VE OPENED THE OUTER HATCH.

159
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:13,636
WISH ME LUCK.

160
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,401
I'M DETECTING SOMETHING
IN THE GAMMA SPECTRUM --

161
00:09:27,401 --> 00:09:30,653
PHASE VARIANT .0075.

162
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:44,834
[ SIGHS ]

163
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:03,019
ITS SURFACE IS POCKMARKED.

164
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:06,314
PROBABLY MICROMETEORITE IMPACTS.

165
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:09,359
IT SEEMS TO HAVE BEEN IN ORBIT
FOR SOME TIME.

166
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:13,738
THE SPIKES ARE MAGNETIC.

167
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:16,991
TWO OF THEM HAVE LOCKED
ONTO THE HULL.

168
00:10:16,991 --> 00:10:20,579
Stand by. I'm gonna run
an internal scan.

169
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:29,796
THERE ARE PROXIMITY SENSORS...

170
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:32,966
BUT THEY APPEAR TO BE OFFLINE.

171
00:10:32,966 --> 00:10:36,636
It looks like the mine
doesn't think it's hit anything.

172
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:39,806
I believe I've found
an access panel.

173
00:10:39,806 --> 00:10:42,476
I'm gonna try and remove it

174
00:10:42,476 --> 00:10:44,852
and get a look inside.

175
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:47,397
HOW BAD IS IT?

176
00:10:47,397 --> 00:10:49,816
I CAN'T REALLY TELL
UNTIL WE CAN GET INTO

177
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:53,612
THE DECOMPRESSED SECTIONS,
BUT I IMAGINE IT'S PRETTY UGLY.

178
00:10:53,612 --> 00:10:57,073
I'VE GOT ONE PIECE
OF GOOD NEWS.

179
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:59,826
I DID A HEAD COUNT.
WE DIDN'T LOSE ANYONE.

180
00:11:02,496 --> 00:11:04,539
TRIP, I'M NOT SURE MALCOLM'S

181
00:11:04,539 --> 00:11:07,125
GONNA BE ABLE TO DEFUSE
THIS THING.

182
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:10,211
COULDN'T WE JUST DETACH
THAT SECTION OF HULL PLATING,

183
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:12,255
LET IT DRIFT AWAY?

184
00:11:12,255 --> 00:11:15,383
WE'D HAVE TO REROUTE
SOME E.P.S. CONDUITS.

185
00:11:15,383 --> 00:11:18,677
THERE'S ABOUT 300
BOLT COUPLINGS.

186
00:11:18,677 --> 00:11:20,305
IT COULD BE DONE.

187
00:11:20,305 --> 00:11:21,556
HOW LONG?

188
00:11:21,556 --> 00:11:23,558
THREE OR FOUR HOURS,

189
00:11:23,558 --> 00:11:25,519
BUT I WOULDN'T
RECOMMEND IT, SIR.

190
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:28,396
WE'D BE EXPOSING A GOOD PIECE
OF THE IMPULSE MANIFOLD.

191
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:30,398
GET A TEAM STARTED.

192
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:33,067
I'LL CONSIDER IT A LAST RESORT.

193
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:39,115
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
Reed: I'm removing the panel.

194
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:44,037
THE ARMING MECHANISM'S
EXTENDING.

195
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:50,877
CAPTAIN.

196
00:11:50,877 --> 00:11:52,920
WE SEE IT, MALCOLM.

197
00:12:00,970 --> 00:12:02,930
ARCHER: EVER SEE
A SHIP LIKE THAT?

198
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:06,476
NO.
IT'S DEFLECTING OUR SCANS.

199
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:08,562
WHY DIDN'T THE BEACONS
LET US SEE THROUGH ITS CLOAK?

200
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:11,606
T'POL: PERHAPS THE MINES USE A
MORE PRIMITIVE CLOAKING SYSTEM.

201
00:12:11,606 --> 00:12:15,109
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
SIR, THEY'RE HAILING US.

202
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:27,622
[<i> MALE SPEAKING</i>
<i>NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

203
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:33,628
THE TRANSLATOR'S NOT LOCKING ON.

204
00:12:38,132 --> 00:12:40,176
ARCHER TO SICK BAY.

205
00:12:41,386 --> 00:12:43,221
YES, CAPTAIN.

206
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:46,516
Is Hoshi in any shape to return
to the bridge? It's urgent.

207
00:12:46,516 --> 00:12:49,603
I'M AFRAID NOT. SHE SUFFERED
A RATHER SEVERE CONCUSSION.

208
00:12:49,603 --> 00:12:51,187
Understood.

209
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:54,107
TELL THEM I'M ON MY WAY.

210
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:56,610
YOU'D BE OF LITTLE HELP IN YOUR
PRESENT CONDITION, ENSIGN.

211
00:12:56,610 --> 00:12:59,195
[ SIGHS ]

212
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:02,240
[<i> MALE SPEAKING</i>
<i>NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

213
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,824
ANY LUCK?

214
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:05,410
NOT YET.

215
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:06,994
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

216
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:08,622
THEY'RE CHARGING WEAPONS.

217
00:13:12,626 --> 00:13:15,962
THEY MISSED OUR STARBOARD
NACELLE BY LESS THAN 20 METERS.

218
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:18,047
NOT A VERY SUBTLE
WARNING SHOT.

219
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:25,012
[<i> SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

220
00:13:25,012 --> 00:13:26,765
CAN YOU GET US OUT OF HERE?

221
00:13:26,765 --> 00:13:29,183
TRAVIS: THE ORBITS OF THOSE
MINES ARE PRETTY ERRATIC, SIR.

222
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:30,435
IT'S GOING TO BE TRICKY.

223
00:13:30,435 --> 00:13:32,979
WE'LL GIVE YOU
WHATEVER HELP WE CAN.

224
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:35,189
BRIDGE TO LIEUTENANT REED.

225
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:36,524
Go ahead.

226
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:39,110
OUR FRIENDS SEEM TO BE ANXIOUS
FOR US TO LEAVE.

227
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:42,113
WE'RE GOING TO BREAK ORBIT
NICE AND SLOWLY.

228
00:13:42,113 --> 00:13:44,031
UNDERSTOOD.

229
00:13:44,031 --> 00:13:47,702
IF YOU PLAN TO GO TO WARP, SIR,
YOU'LL LET ME KNOW?

230
00:13:47,702 --> 00:13:49,579
I'll try to remember.

231
00:13:49,579 --> 00:13:52,165
-MANEUVERING THRUSTERS ONLY.
-AYE, SIR.

232
00:13:56,127 --> 00:13:58,171
ARCHER: ACTIVATE THE BEACON.

233
00:14:16,523 --> 00:14:18,399
OUR FRIENDS JUST VANISHED.

234
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:21,277
Archer: That doesn't mean
they're not still close.

235
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:37,752
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
Lieutenant Reed to bridge.

236
00:14:37,752 --> 00:14:39,212
GO AHEAD.

237
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:42,965
I'VE IDENTIFIED FOUR SEPARATE
DETONATION CIRCUITS.

238
00:14:44,509 --> 00:14:47,512
IF I CAN ISOLATE THEM
IN THE PROPER SEQUENCE,

239
00:14:47,512 --> 00:14:50,515
I SHOULD BE ABLE
TO DEACTIVATE THE MINE.

240
00:14:50,515 --> 00:14:53,434
IT'LL TAKE SOME DOING.

241
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:57,522
AND TO BE HONEST, CAPTAIN,
IT'S ONLY A THEORY.

242
00:14:57,522 --> 00:14:59,440
HOW GOOD A THEORY?

243
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,526
The closest thing
I'm familiar with

244
00:15:01,526 --> 00:15:03,110
that this device resembles

245
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:05,655
is a Triton-class
spatial torpedo.

246
00:15:05,655 --> 00:15:08,366
I'VE DISARMED AT LEAST
HALF A DOZEN OF THOSE.

247
00:15:08,366 --> 00:15:10,993
I BELIEVE I CAN DO IT, SIR.

248
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:14,038
I'VE GOT TRIP WORKING
ON A BACKUP PLAN,

249
00:15:14,038 --> 00:15:17,667
BUT I'D PREFER NOT TO USE IT.

250
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:20,754
RIGHT NOW, YOU'RE OUR BEST BET.

251
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:24,173
BE CAREFUL, MALCOLM.

252
00:15:28,762 --> 00:15:30,430
I SEE IT.

253
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:36,185
AAH!

254
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:40,899
[ GROANING ]

255
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:46,446
BRIDGE.

256
00:15:46,446 --> 00:15:48,030
GO AHEAD.

257
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:50,408
Another one of those spikes
I told you about.

258
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:51,618
WHAT ABOUT IT?

259
00:15:51,618 --> 00:15:54,871
IT JUST MAGNETIZED ITSELF
TO THE HULL.

260
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:56,664
Is there a problem?

261
00:15:56,664 --> 00:15:59,292
ON ITS WAY...
[ COUGHS ]

262
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:01,377
IT WENT THROUGH MY LEG, SIR.

263
00:16:01,377 --> 00:16:03,671
I'M ON MY WAY, LIEUTENANT.
THE BRIDGE IS YOURS.

264
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:06,424
CAPTAIN, I SHOULD BE THE ONE
TO GO OUT THERE.

265
00:16:06,424 --> 00:16:08,008
I'M THE ENGINEER.

266
00:16:08,008 --> 00:16:09,761
THAT'S WHY I NEED YOU
HERE, TRIP.

267
00:16:11,095 --> 00:16:13,306
YOU'LL HAVE TO WAIT IN LINE
FOR MY OSMOTIC EEL

268
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,350
TO CAUTERIZE YOUR WOUND; HE'S
GETTING QUITE A WORKOUT TODAY.

269
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,352
-DOCTOR.
-ENSIGN.

270
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:20,939
THEY NEED A TRANSLATOR.
I SHOULD BE AT MY POST.

271
00:16:20,939 --> 00:16:22,607
I REALIZE YOU'RE
ANXIOUS TO HELP,

272
00:16:22,607 --> 00:16:24,567
BUT YOU WOULDN'T MAKE IT
TO THE TURBOLIFT.

273
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:27,904
IF YOU'D LIKE, I COULD HAVE THEM
BRING THE COM LOGS HERE.

274
00:16:27,904 --> 00:16:30,573
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

275
00:16:33,868 --> 00:16:36,496
ARCHER: THOUGHT YOU
MIGHT NEED A HAND.

276
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:41,125
ACTUALLY...I'D PREFER A LEG.

277
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:45,546
LET'S SEE WHAT WE CAN DO
WITH THE ONE YOU GOT.

278
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:57,725
COULD HAVE BEEN WORSE.
IT MISSED THE BONE.

279
00:16:57,725 --> 00:16:59,769
AND IT LOOKS LIKE THE PRESSURE
FROM THE SPIKE IS

280
00:16:59,769 --> 00:17:01,771
KEEPING THE WOUND
FROM BLEEDING TOO MUCH.

281
00:17:01,771 --> 00:17:04,440
YOU'LL BE IN SICK BAY
IN NO TIME.

282
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:06,693
THESE SHOULD CUT
RIGHT THROUGH IT.

283
00:17:06,693 --> 00:17:10,029
REED: ACTUALLY, SIR,
I WOULDN'T DO THAT.

284
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:14,575
MY SCANS SHOW DETONATION
CIRCUITS INSIDE THE SPIKES.

285
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:16,452
I WOULD CONSIDER

286
00:17:16,452 --> 00:17:18,454
LETTING YOU AMPUTATE,

287
00:17:18,454 --> 00:17:20,581
BUT IF CHEF GOT HOLD OF IT,

288
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:23,417
HE'D BE SERVING
ROAST REED FOR SUNDAY DINNER.

289
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:25,127
-[ CHUCKLES ]
-JUST GIVE ME

290
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:26,671
SOMETHING FOR THE PAIN,

291
00:17:26,671 --> 00:17:29,590
AND I'LL DO MY BEST
TO REACH THE ACCESS PANEL.

292
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:32,426
NOT WITHOUT DOING MORE DAMAGE
TO THAT LEG.

293
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:34,470
WHAT'S MORE IMPORTANT --

294
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:38,016
MY LEG OR YOUR SHIP?

295
00:17:38,016 --> 00:17:40,601
I INTEND TO SAVE BOTH.

296
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:42,228
I DON'T SEE HOW.

297
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:45,314
ARCHER: THAT BACKUP PLAN
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT --

298
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:47,233
I ASKED TRIP TO PREPARE

299
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:50,236
TO DETACH THIS SECTION
OF HULL PLATING.

300
00:17:50,236 --> 00:17:52,947
SEEMED LIKE A GOOD IDEA
AT THE TIME.

301
00:17:52,947 --> 00:17:55,115
IT'S STILL A GOOD IDEA.

302
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:58,494
NOT WITH YOU
ATTACHED TO IT.

303
00:17:58,494 --> 00:18:00,454
I HOPE THAT'S AN ANESTHETIC.

304
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:03,082
PHLOX'S OWN RECIPE.

305
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:06,878
[ REED SIGHS ]

306
00:18:06,878 --> 00:18:08,880
[ CHUCKLES ]

307
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:11,090
PLEASE, SIR,

308
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:13,217
MAY I HAVE SOME MORE?

309
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:15,929
ARCHER: I DON'T WANT YOU
TOO SEDATED.

310
00:18:15,929 --> 00:18:18,723
I'M GONNA NEED YOUR HELP.

311
00:18:18,723 --> 00:18:22,476
SOMEONE'S GOT
TO DEFUSE THIS THING.

312
00:18:22,476 --> 00:18:25,104
YOU'RE GONNA TALK ME THROUGH IT.

313
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:27,481
REED: WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,
CAPTAIN,

314
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:31,444
DISARMING MINES
IS EXTREMELY DELICATE BUSINESS.

315
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:33,905
I'M TRAINED FOR IT.

316
00:18:33,905 --> 00:18:36,323
YOU'RE NOT.

317
00:18:36,323 --> 00:18:39,953
ARCHER: I'M A QUICK STUDY.

318
00:18:39,953 --> 00:18:42,663
REED: IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.

319
00:18:44,331 --> 00:18:46,960
ARCHER: IN CASE YOU HAVEN'T
NOTICED, LIEUTENANT,

320
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:50,713
WE'RE SITTING ABOUT FIVE METERS
FROM AN IMPULSE REACTOR.

321
00:18:52,590 --> 00:18:55,843
I'M NOT LEAVING TILL
WE TAKE THIS WEAPON OFFLINE.

322
00:18:55,843 --> 00:18:57,386
SIR --

323
00:18:57,386 --> 00:19:01,057
THE WAY I SEE IT,
YOU DON'T HAVE MUCH CHOICE.

324
00:19:01,057 --> 00:19:02,850
YOU'RE SORT OF STUCK HERE,

325
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:05,937
SO WOULD YOU
LET ME GET STARTED?

326
00:19:09,857 --> 00:19:12,986
REED: I HOPE YOU'VE GOT
A STEADY HAND.

327
00:19:28,918 --> 00:19:32,254
THEY'RE ORDERING US TO LEAVE
THEIR SYSTEM IMMEDIATELY,

328
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:33,923
OR THEY'LL DESTROY US.

329
00:19:33,923 --> 00:19:35,382
CHARMING.

330
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:37,343
COULD YOU FIGURE OUT A WAY
TO COMPOSE A MESSAGE BACK

331
00:19:37,343 --> 00:19:40,304
EXPLAINING...WE'RE GOING
AS FAST AS WE CAN?

332
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:42,306
I CAN TRY.

333
00:19:43,474 --> 00:19:45,852
T'POL: AND THEIR NEXT MESSAGE?

334
00:19:45,852 --> 00:19:47,895
THEY SAY THEY'VE
ANNEXED THIS PLANET

335
00:19:47,895 --> 00:19:51,983
IN THE NAME OF SOMETHING CALLED
THE ROMALIN STAR EMPIRE.

336
00:19:51,983 --> 00:19:54,694
T'POL: ROMULAN.

337
00:19:54,694 --> 00:19:58,405
IT'S PRONOUNCED ROMULAN.

338
00:20:04,787 --> 00:20:06,372
ARCHER: ROMULANS?

339
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:08,708
I READ ABOUT THEM
WHEN I WAS WITH DANIELS.

340
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,376
Tucker: What'd you find out?

341
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:11,878
NOT MUCH. JUST THE NAME.

342
00:20:11,878 --> 00:20:14,505
H-HE WOULDN'T LET ME
SEE ANYTHING ELSE. T'POL?

343
00:20:14,505 --> 00:20:18,051
T'POL: THEY'RE RUMORED TO BE AN
AGGRESSIVE, TERRITORIAL SPECIES,

344
00:20:18,051 --> 00:20:19,719
BUT THE VULCAN HIGH COMMAND
HAS NEVER MADE

345
00:20:19,719 --> 00:20:21,679
DIRECT CONTACT WITH THEM.

346
00:20:21,679 --> 00:20:24,264
ENSIGN SATO'S TRANSLATION SAYS

347
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:25,933
THAT THEY'RE DEMANDING
THAT WE WITHDRAW

348
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,852
from this system immediately.

349
00:20:27,852 --> 00:20:30,104
THAT'S GONNA BE A LITTLE
TOUGH TO DO AT THE MOMENT.

350
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:33,024
IS THERE ANY WAY YOU CAN EXPLAIN
OUR SITUATION?

351
00:20:33,024 --> 00:20:37,236
SHE BELIEVES SHE'LL HAVE A REPLY
PREPARED WITHIN THE HOUR.

352
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:39,572
HOW'S IT GOING OUT THERE,
CAPTAIN?

353
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:42,616
We've taken two of
the detonation circuits offline.

354
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:45,703
Three more to go.
Keep me posted.

355
00:20:47,872 --> 00:20:50,583
REED: THE NEXT ONE'S GOING
TO BE TRICKY.

356
00:20:50,583 --> 00:20:52,626
DO YOU SEE
THE Y-SHAPED COMPONENTS

357
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:54,670
SURROUNDING THE CIRCUIT?

358
00:20:58,049 --> 00:21:00,051
THERE'S SIX OF THEM.

359
00:21:00,051 --> 00:21:03,679
REED: RIGHT.
THOSE ARE TIMING RELAYS.

360
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:05,932
YOU'LL HAVE TO ROTATE EACH ONE

361
00:21:05,932 --> 00:21:09,518
COUNTERCLOCKWISE 70 DEGREES.

362
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:12,479
BUT IT HAS TO BE DONE
IN THE PROPER ORDER.

363
00:21:12,479 --> 00:21:14,607
I'LL GUIDE YOU THROUGH IT.

364
00:21:14,607 --> 00:21:18,236
START WITH THE RELAY
TO YOUR UPPER RIGHT.

365
00:21:18,236 --> 00:21:20,529
ONE CENTIMETER.

366
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:23,908
AND THEN TURN IT 70 DEGREES

367
00:21:23,908 --> 00:21:25,952
COUNTERCLOCKWISE.

368
00:21:29,872 --> 00:21:31,165
GOOD.

369
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:35,086
NOW PULL IT OUT, SLOWLY.

370
00:21:35,086 --> 00:21:38,297
BE CAREFUL NOT TO TOUCH
THE HOUSING.

371
00:21:47,014 --> 00:21:49,433
REED: WELL DONE.

372
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:52,853
NOW COMPLETE THAT SET
ON THE DIAGONAL.

373
00:21:55,522 --> 00:21:57,108
SO WHERE WERE WE?

374
00:21:57,108 --> 00:21:58,692
SIR?

375
00:21:58,692 --> 00:22:00,736
ARCHER: THIS MORNING
AT BREAKFAST,

376
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:03,156
BEFORE WE WERE INTERRUPTED.

377
00:22:03,156 --> 00:22:07,743
YOU SAID YOU DIDN'T FOLLOW
ANY PARTICULAR SPORT.

378
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:10,871
WELL, I'M AFRAID I HAVEN'T
STARTED FOLLOWING ONE

379
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:13,040
SINCE BREAKFAST, SIR.

380
00:22:14,374 --> 00:22:15,584
[ ARCHER SIGHS ]

381
00:22:15,584 --> 00:22:19,213
REED: NOW, GO
TO THE RELAY TOP CENTER.

382
00:22:19,213 --> 00:22:23,176
BUT WATCH THAT ONE.
I BELIEVE IT MAY BE DAMAGED.

383
00:22:23,176 --> 00:22:27,305
IT'LL NEED SOME EXTRA TORQUE
TO DEACTIVATE IT.

384
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:31,100
HOW ABOUT HOBBIES?

385
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:33,102
ARCHER: ANY HOBBIES?

386
00:22:33,102 --> 00:22:34,979
NO. NOT REALLY, SIR.

387
00:22:34,979 --> 00:22:36,480
ARCHER: COULD'VE SWORN
I'VE SEEN YOU READING

388
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,065
A BOOK OR TWO
IN THE MESS HALL.

389
00:22:38,065 --> 00:22:41,194
SIR...DO YOU REALLY THINK

390
00:22:41,194 --> 00:22:43,863
THAT THIS IS THE APPROPRIATE
TIME FOR A CHAT?

391
00:22:43,863 --> 00:22:47,616
IT HELPS ME FOCUS.
IT CALMS MY NERVES.

392
00:22:47,616 --> 00:22:49,660
WELL, IT ISN'T CALMING MINE.

393
00:22:49,660 --> 00:22:51,620
ARCHER: SORRY.

394
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:54,123
IT MADE YOU A LITTLE NERVOUS
THIS MORNING, TOO,

395
00:22:54,123 --> 00:22:56,583
DIDN'T IT? WHY IS THAT?

396
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:59,461
IF YOU MUST KNOW...

397
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:02,506
I<i> WAS</i> HONORED TO BE ASKED
TO SIT AT YOUR TABLE.

398
00:23:02,506 --> 00:23:05,176
I JUST WASN'T ENTIRELY
COMFORTABLE

399
00:23:05,176 --> 00:23:09,180
HAVING A CASUAL MEAL
WITH MY CAPTAIN.

400
00:23:09,180 --> 00:23:12,350
I WAS TRAINED NOT TO FRATERNIZE
WITH SUPERIOR OFFICERS.

401
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:15,269
NEVER TOO LATE TO LEARN.

402
00:23:15,269 --> 00:23:18,272
FRANKLY, SIR,
FROM MY POINT OF VIEW,

403
00:23:18,272 --> 00:23:22,068
THAT KIND OF SOCIALIZING HAS
NO PLACE ON A STARSHIP.

404
00:23:22,068 --> 00:23:25,445
I HAD A C.O. ONCE,
FELT THE SAME WAY --

405
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:28,574
"THEY'RE YOUR CREW,
NOT YOUR FRIENDS."

406
00:23:30,034 --> 00:23:32,452
I THOUGHT ABOUT THAT A LOT

407
00:23:32,452 --> 00:23:35,413
WHEN I TOOK THIS COMMAND.

408
00:23:35,413 --> 00:23:38,542
BUT THEN I REALIZED THIS IS NOT
YOUR TYPICAL MISSION.

409
00:23:38,542 --> 00:23:41,754
ARCHER: WE COULD BE
OUT HERE FOR YEARS.

410
00:23:41,754 --> 00:23:46,384
ALL WE HAVE TO DEPEND ON...
IS EACH OTHER.

411
00:23:50,512 --> 00:23:51,889
[ SIGHS ]

412
00:23:51,889 --> 00:23:53,807
THERE ARE TWO LEFT.

413
00:23:53,807 --> 00:23:55,726
TOP LEFT FIRST.

414
00:23:56,894 --> 00:24:01,148
I APPRECIATE YOUR SUGGESTIONS,
MALCOLM.

415
00:24:01,148 --> 00:24:03,150
ANYTHING ELSE?

416
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:06,946
WELL...SINCE YOU ASKED...

417
00:24:06,946 --> 00:24:09,949
BRIDGE PROTOCOLS
HAVE BECOME SOMEWHAT LAX.

418
00:24:09,949 --> 00:24:13,244
TOO MANY PEOPLE
OFFERING OPINIONS.

419
00:24:13,244 --> 00:24:16,163
WE'RE HERE TO CARRY OUT
YOUR ORDERS, SIR.

420
00:24:16,163 --> 00:24:17,748
YOU'RE THE CAPTAIN.

421
00:24:17,748 --> 00:24:19,792
WHAT'S THE POINT
OF HAVING A SENIOR STAFF

422
00:24:19,792 --> 00:24:22,836
IF THEY JUST SIT AROUND
WITH THEIR MOUTHS SHUT?

423
00:24:22,836 --> 00:24:25,839
GLAD THEY HAVE OPINIONS.

424
00:24:25,839 --> 00:24:28,301
I RELY ON THEM.

425
00:24:28,301 --> 00:24:30,344
AHH.

426
00:24:31,762 --> 00:24:33,764
KEEP GOING.

427
00:24:33,764 --> 00:24:37,726
AND IN THE AREA OF SECURITY,

428
00:24:37,726 --> 00:24:42,106
I SOMETIMES THINK YOU COULD SHOW
A LITTLE MORE...CAUTION, SIR.

429
00:24:42,106 --> 00:24:45,234
I'M AWARE OF YOUR CONCERNS
IN THAT AREA.

430
00:24:45,234 --> 00:24:47,736
NOT TO SAY THAT IT
HASN'T BEEN A PRIVILEGE

431
00:24:47,736 --> 00:24:48,988
TO HAVE SERVED WITH YOU.

432
00:24:48,988 --> 00:24:50,530
UNH-UNH!

433
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:52,074
SIR?

434
00:24:52,074 --> 00:24:54,994
ARCHER: YOU'RE TALKING
IN THE PAST TENSE, LIEUTENANT.

435
00:25:02,168 --> 00:25:06,588
NOW...REINSERT ALL SIX RELAYS,

436
00:25:06,588 --> 00:25:09,133
BUT IN THE REVERSE ORDER.

437
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:20,269
YOU'RE DOING FINE, SIR.

438
00:25:20,269 --> 00:25:22,480
THANKS.

439
00:25:33,199 --> 00:25:35,159
[ SIGHS ]

440
00:25:35,159 --> 00:25:37,870
YOU'VE EARNED
YOURSELF A BREAK, TRAVIS.

441
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:41,207
ENSIGN HUTCHISON CAN COVER
THE HELM FOR A WHILE.

442
00:25:41,207 --> 00:25:45,044
THANK YOU, SIR, BUT I'D PREFER
TO STAY AT MY POST.

443
00:25:45,044 --> 00:25:46,879
BRIDGE TO CAPTAIN ARCHER.

444
00:25:46,879 --> 00:25:48,839
Archer: Go ahead.

445
00:25:48,839 --> 00:25:50,883
WE'RE CLEAR OF THE MINEFIELD.

446
00:25:50,883 --> 00:25:53,511
MAINTAIN COURSE AND SPEED.

447
00:25:53,511 --> 00:25:55,179
Understood.

448
00:25:57,473 --> 00:26:00,518
REED: THIS LAST
DETONATION CIRCUIT

449
00:26:00,518 --> 00:26:03,062
HAS AN ADDED ATTRACTION.

450
00:26:03,062 --> 00:26:05,772
I'M SEEING SOMETHING
THAT LOOKS LIKE

451
00:26:05,772 --> 00:26:08,234
A BACKUP ARMING MECHANISM.

452
00:26:08,234 --> 00:26:09,402
[ GRUNTS ]

453
00:26:09,402 --> 00:26:11,028
WE'LL HAVE TO FOOL
THE CIRCUIT

454
00:26:11,028 --> 00:26:13,739
INTO THINKING
IT'S STILL ONLINE.

455
00:26:13,739 --> 00:26:15,866
ARCHER: HOW DO WE DO THAT?

456
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:18,994
THERE'S A HYPERSPANNER
IN THE EQUIPMENT CASE.

457
00:26:18,994 --> 00:26:23,040
TAKE OUT ITS POWER CELL
AND STRIP OFF THE CASING.

458
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,583
ARCHER: YOU MUST HAVE REALIZED

459
00:26:25,583 --> 00:26:29,671
THIS WASN'T GOING TO BE
YOUR TYPICAL ARMORY POSTING,

460
00:26:29,671 --> 00:26:32,883
THAT MY...COMMAND STYLE

461
00:26:32,883 --> 00:26:36,262
LACKED A CERTAIN
SPIT AND POLISH.

462
00:26:36,262 --> 00:26:40,391
IT<i> WAS</i> OBVIOUS...
IF YOU DON'T MIND ME SAYING SO.

463
00:26:40,391 --> 00:26:42,393
[ CHUCKLES ]

464
00:26:42,393 --> 00:26:43,977
STRANGE.

465
00:26:43,977 --> 00:26:45,979
WHAT'S STRANGE, SIR?

466
00:26:45,979 --> 00:26:47,189
ARCHER: I UNDERSTAND YOU CAME

467
00:26:47,189 --> 00:26:49,983
FROM A LONG LINE
OF ROYAL NAVY MEN.

468
00:26:49,983 --> 00:26:53,487
YOUR FATHER, YOUR GRANDFATHER.

469
00:26:53,487 --> 00:26:55,072
WHY PICK STARFLEET?

470
00:26:55,072 --> 00:26:58,033
WHY NOT CONTINUE
THE FAMILY TRADITION?

471
00:26:58,033 --> 00:27:00,660
GOD KNOWS I TRIED.

472
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:02,079
WHAT HAPPENED?

473
00:27:02,079 --> 00:27:04,915
I'LL NEED A CIRCUIT PROBE.

474
00:27:16,676 --> 00:27:18,887
[ SIGHS ]

475
00:27:25,561 --> 00:27:27,938
SO WHAT HAPPENED?

476
00:27:27,938 --> 00:27:30,983
I WAS RAISED ON THE WATER.

477
00:27:32,192 --> 00:27:34,194
I KNEW HOW TO HANDLE A BOAT

478
00:27:34,194 --> 00:27:37,156
BEFORE I COULD RIDE A BICYCLE.

479
00:27:37,156 --> 00:27:39,783
STUDIED ALL
THE GREAT NAVAL BATTLES.

480
00:27:39,783 --> 00:27:42,369
I DON'T KNOW.

481
00:27:42,369 --> 00:27:46,039
I SUPPOSE I THOUGHT
I'D JUST GROW OUT OF IT.

482
00:27:46,039 --> 00:27:48,041
GROW OUT OF WHAT?

483
00:27:49,585 --> 00:27:52,045
AQUAPHOBIA.

484
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:55,007
YOU'RE AFRAID OF THE WATER?

485
00:27:55,007 --> 00:27:57,217
MORE PRECISELY,

486
00:27:57,217 --> 00:27:59,428
AFRAID OF DROWNING.

487
00:27:59,428 --> 00:28:01,847
SO...

488
00:28:01,847 --> 00:28:04,433
INSTEAD OF A LIFE

489
00:28:04,433 --> 00:28:08,521
ON THE SEA, YOU CHOSE
A LIFE IN THE VACUUM OF SPACE?

490
00:28:18,238 --> 00:28:20,073
[ REED SIGHS ]

491
00:28:20,073 --> 00:28:21,992
I HAD A GREAT-UNCLE

492
00:28:21,992 --> 00:28:25,078
WHO SUFFERED
FROM THE SAME PROBLEM...

493
00:28:26,622 --> 00:28:29,333
BUT HE FACED HIS FEARS.

494
00:28:29,333 --> 00:28:31,335
JOINED THE NAVY,

495
00:28:31,335 --> 00:28:34,588
HAD A DISTINGUISHED CAREER.

496
00:28:34,588 --> 00:28:37,216
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO

497
00:28:37,216 --> 00:28:40,135
IS ATTACH IT TO THE CYLINDER

498
00:28:40,135 --> 00:28:42,262
ON YOUR UPPER RIGHT.

499
00:28:46,016 --> 00:28:47,434
[ BEEPING ]

500
00:28:47,434 --> 00:28:48,852
IT'S WORKING.

501
00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:51,355
START WITH THE TOPMOST
COMPONENT.

502
00:28:51,355 --> 00:28:54,733
USE THE CALIPER TO LIFT IT
A FEW MILLIMETERS,

503
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:59,238
AND THEN TURN IT
CLOCKWISE 360 DEGREES,

504
00:28:59,238 --> 00:29:01,490
AND THEN GENTLY REINSERT IT.

505
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:06,828
HE WAS SOMETHING
OF A HERO TO ME,

506
00:29:06,828 --> 00:29:08,830
MY GREAT-UNCLE.

507
00:29:08,830 --> 00:29:11,041
THE ONE WITH AQUAPHOBIA?

508
00:29:11,041 --> 00:29:12,543
REED: INDEED.

509
00:29:12,543 --> 00:29:15,671
HE SIGNED UP
WITH THE SUBMARINE SERVICE.

510
00:29:15,671 --> 00:29:18,924
ARCHER: TALK ABOUT FACING
YOUR DEEPEST FEARS.

511
00:29:18,924 --> 00:29:21,594
HE WAS A BRAVE MAN.

512
00:29:23,429 --> 00:29:26,473
WASN'T LONG BEFORE HE'D WORKED
HIS WAY UP THROUGH THE RANKS,

513
00:29:26,473 --> 00:29:29,602
MADE CHIEF ENGINEER
ON THE H.M.S.<i> CLEMENT.</i>

514
00:29:30,852 --> 00:29:33,564
DO YOU KNOW THE STORY
OF THE<i> CLEMENT,</i> SIR?

515
00:29:33,564 --> 00:29:37,359
I DON'T THINK I DO.

516
00:29:38,527 --> 00:29:39,737
REED: GOOD.

517
00:29:39,737 --> 00:29:43,823
NOW...THE OTHER FIVE
COMPONENTS.

518
00:29:44,991 --> 00:29:47,661
REPEAT THE SAME PROCESS
ON EACH ONE,

519
00:29:47,661 --> 00:29:49,705
COUNTERCLOCKWISE.

520
00:29:51,498 --> 00:29:54,251
YOU WERE TELLING ME
ABOUT THE<i> CLEMENT.</i>

521
00:29:55,461 --> 00:29:58,088
THEY WERE ON A ROUTINE PATROL

522
00:29:58,088 --> 00:30:00,758
WHEN THEY HAD AN ACCIDENT.

523
00:30:02,968 --> 00:30:06,597
NOW, THERE'S A BEAUTIFUL IRONY
FOR YOU.

524
00:30:06,597 --> 00:30:08,432
THEY HIT A MINE...

525
00:30:08,432 --> 00:30:10,934
LEFT OVER FROM SOME WORLD WAR.

526
00:30:12,436 --> 00:30:14,062
REED: THERE THEY WERE,

527
00:30:14,062 --> 00:30:17,691
TRAPPED UNDERNEATH AN ICE SHELF,

528
00:30:17,691 --> 00:30:19,693
SEVERAL COMPARTMENTS FLOODING,

529
00:30:19,693 --> 00:30:22,154
INCLUDING ENGINEERING.

530
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:25,532
CAN YOU IMAGINE?

531
00:30:25,532 --> 00:30:28,118
MY GREAT-UNCLE...

532
00:30:28,118 --> 00:30:30,663
THE MAN AFRAID OF DROWNING.

533
00:30:30,663 --> 00:30:33,791
REED: THE SHIP WAS SINKING,

534
00:30:33,791 --> 00:30:35,793
LOSING POWER.

535
00:30:35,793 --> 00:30:38,754
ACCORDING TO HIS LIEUTENANT...

536
00:30:38,754 --> 00:30:43,383
MY GREAT-UNCLE SEALED HIMSELF
IN THE ENGINE ROOM

537
00:30:43,383 --> 00:30:46,386
AND KEPT THE REACTOR ONLINE
LONG ENOUGH

538
00:30:46,386 --> 00:30:50,474
FOR HIS CREW TO MAKE IT
TO THE ESCAPE PODS.

539
00:30:53,435 --> 00:30:56,438
HE WENT DOWN WITH HIS SHIP.

540
00:30:56,438 --> 00:30:58,440
HE DID WHAT HE HAD TO DO

541
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:01,109
TO SAVE HIS CREWMATES.

542
00:31:01,109 --> 00:31:04,822
I APPRECIATE WHAT YOU'RE TRYING
TO TELL ME, MALCOLM...

543
00:31:04,822 --> 00:31:07,491
BUT I WAS HOPING...

544
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:12,830
YOU'D BE ABLE TO SAVE
YOUR HEROICS FOR ANOTHER TIME.

545
00:31:12,830 --> 00:31:15,457
I JUST WANT YOU TO KNOW, SIR,

546
00:31:15,457 --> 00:31:17,751
THAT I AM PREPARED.

547
00:31:17,751 --> 00:31:19,545
GOT YOU.

548
00:31:19,545 --> 00:31:22,255
IF WE'RE NOT ABLE
TO DEFUSE THIS MINE,

549
00:31:22,255 --> 00:31:24,299
THE SAFETY OF THE CREW
HAS TO --

550
00:31:24,299 --> 00:31:26,635
I SAID I HEARD YOU, LIEUTENANT.

551
00:31:35,101 --> 00:31:37,813
I'M AFRAID WE HAVE
ANOTHER PROBLEM, SIR.

552
00:31:37,813 --> 00:31:40,607
WHAT? WHAT IS IT?

553
00:31:41,941 --> 00:31:44,862
I NEED TO USE THE BATHROOM.

554
00:31:46,530 --> 00:31:48,615
I WON'T TELL A SOUL.

555
00:31:49,949 --> 00:31:52,118
IN MY E.V. SUIT, SIR?

556
00:31:54,246 --> 00:31:56,665
[ LAUGHTER ]

557
00:32:04,757 --> 00:32:06,425
SIR.

558
00:32:12,222 --> 00:32:15,350
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
WE'RE BEING HAILED.

559
00:32:17,227 --> 00:32:20,272
<i>YOU'VE IGNORED OUR WARNINGS.</i>

560
00:32:20,272 --> 00:32:22,357
WE WERE UNABLE
TO TRANSLATE YOUR LANGUAGE

561
00:32:22,357 --> 00:32:24,234
UNTIL A SHORT TIME AGO.

562
00:32:24,234 --> 00:32:26,737
WE'RE TRYING TO DEFUSE A WEAPON
LODGED ON OUR HULL.

563
00:32:26,737 --> 00:32:28,947
<i>I'M WELL AWARE</i>
<i>OF YOUR SITUATION.</i>

564
00:32:28,947 --> 00:32:32,534
<i>OUR SCANS SHOW YOU'RE PREPARED</i>
<i>TO DETACH THE HULL SEGMENT</i>

565
00:32:32,534 --> 00:32:33,786
<i>SURROUNDING THE MINE.</i>

566
00:32:33,786 --> 00:32:35,328
<i>COMPLETE THE PROCEDURE</i>

567
00:32:35,328 --> 00:32:38,373
<i>AND LEAVE THIS SYSTEM</i>
<i>IMMEDIATELY.</i>

568
00:32:38,373 --> 00:32:41,042
WE'VE GOT A MAN
TRAPPED OUT THERE.

569
00:32:41,042 --> 00:32:43,253
DON'T YOUR SCANS SHOW YOU THAT?

570
00:32:43,253 --> 00:32:44,755
<i>ONE CREWMAN.</i>

571
00:32:44,755 --> 00:32:47,215
<i>YOU HAVE 82 OTHERS</i>
<i>SAFELY ABOARD.</i>

572
00:32:47,215 --> 00:32:50,510
<i>JETTISON THE HULL SEGMENT</i>
<i>AND LEAVE.</i>

573
00:32:50,510 --> 00:32:52,971
<i>WE WILL NOT TOLERATE ESPIONAGE.</i>

574
00:32:52,971 --> 00:32:55,557
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

575
00:32:55,557 --> 00:32:57,643
Archer: T'Pol, report.

576
00:32:59,561 --> 00:33:01,563
THEY'RE DEMANDING

577
00:33:01,563 --> 00:33:04,650
THAT WE JETTISON THE SECTION
OF THE HULL PLATING AND LEAVE.

578
00:33:04,650 --> 00:33:06,151
THEY SCANNED US, CAPTAIN.

579
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:08,153
THEY KNOW WE'RE READY
TO DETACH IT.

580
00:33:08,153 --> 00:33:11,281
ARCHER: I'M DEFUSING
THE LAST DETONATION CIRCUIT.

581
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:15,285
STAND BY.

582
00:33:38,099 --> 00:33:39,768
IT'S REARMING!

583
00:33:39,768 --> 00:33:41,937
REED: RESET THAT LAST COMPONENT!

584
00:33:41,937 --> 00:33:43,438
QUICKLY!

585
00:33:58,620 --> 00:34:00,205
LIEUTENANT?

586
00:34:00,205 --> 00:34:03,834
WHEN YOU DEACTIVATED
THAT FINAL CIRCUIT,

587
00:34:03,834 --> 00:34:06,461
IT TRIGGERED A SUB-DETONATOR.

588
00:34:06,461 --> 00:34:09,172
HOW CAN WE GET TO IT?

589
00:34:09,172 --> 00:34:11,174
WE CAN'T.

590
00:34:11,174 --> 00:34:13,134
IT'S TOO DEEP INSIDE.

591
00:34:13,134 --> 00:34:16,471
WE'D HAVE TO DISMANTLE
THE ENTIRE MINE.

592
00:34:17,931 --> 00:34:19,933
REED: CAPTAIN...

593
00:34:19,933 --> 00:34:23,061
THOSE HEROICS WE SPOKE ABOUT.

594
00:34:25,605 --> 00:34:28,191
I THINK IT MAY BE TIME.

595
00:34:36,575 --> 00:34:39,578
YOU'VE DONE ALL YOU CAN, SIR.

596
00:34:39,578 --> 00:34:42,121
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,

597
00:34:42,121 --> 00:34:44,249
YOU'D MAKE A FINE
ARMORY OFFICER.

598
00:34:44,249 --> 00:34:45,792
SHOW ME THAT SUB-DETONATOR.

599
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:47,753
REED: I'D PREFER
A BURIAL AT SEA

600
00:34:47,753 --> 00:34:49,796
IF I'M NOT
COMPLETELY VAPORIZED.

601
00:34:49,796 --> 00:34:51,965
ARCHER: I THOUGHT YOU WERE
AFRAID OF THE WATER.

602
00:34:51,965 --> 00:34:53,675
YOUR SCANNER, LIEUTENANT.

603
00:34:53,675 --> 00:34:55,635
I TOLD YOU, SIR.

604
00:34:55,635 --> 00:34:57,846
THERE'S NOTHING WE CAN DO.

605
00:34:57,846 --> 00:35:01,391
WE'LL DISMANTLE THIS THING
PIECE BY PIECE IF WE HAVE TO.

606
00:35:01,391 --> 00:35:03,643
THAT'LL TAKE DAYS.

607
00:35:03,643 --> 00:35:04,937
MY SCHEDULE'S OPEN.

608
00:35:04,937 --> 00:35:06,479
REED: AND THESE ROMULANS --

609
00:35:06,479 --> 00:35:08,899
THEY DON'T SEEM
LIKE THE PATIENT TYPES.

610
00:35:08,899 --> 00:35:11,068
REED: THE LONGER WE STAY
IN THIS SYSTEM,

611
00:35:11,068 --> 00:35:13,737
THE MORE LIKELY
THEY'RE GOING TO ATTACK.

612
00:35:13,737 --> 00:35:16,364
AS MUCH AS I APPRECIATE
ALL YOUR EFFORTS,

613
00:35:16,364 --> 00:35:19,200
YOU HAVE TO DETACH
THE HULL PLATING.

614
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:21,160
IT'S THE ONLY OPTION.

615
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:23,496
I'M NOT ABOUT TO LEAVE
ONE OF MY CREW BEHIND.

616
00:35:23,496 --> 00:35:25,958
YOU'RE PUTTING<i> ENTERPRISE</i> 
AT RISK.

617
00:35:25,958 --> 00:35:27,960
ARCHER: WE'RE WASTING TIME!

618
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:30,420
HELP ME FIGURE OUT A WAY
TO GET YOU OFF OF HERE.

619
00:35:30,420 --> 00:35:32,714
THAT'S AN ORDER.

620
00:35:34,466 --> 00:35:37,010
[ AIR HISSING ]

621
00:35:37,010 --> 00:35:39,012
[ GRUNTS ]

622
00:35:40,263 --> 00:35:42,766
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?

623
00:36:02,535 --> 00:36:04,579
ARCHER: GREAT.

624
00:36:16,091 --> 00:36:18,510
[ AIR HISSES ]

625
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:20,762
IF I WERE THE KIND OF CAPTAIN
YOU THINK I SHOULD BE,

626
00:36:20,762 --> 00:36:22,848
I'D BUST YOUR ASS
BACK TO CREWMAN.

627
00:36:22,848 --> 00:36:24,808
BEGGING YOUR PARDON, SIR,

628
00:36:24,808 --> 00:36:26,977
BUT IF YOU WERE
THAT KIND OF CAPTAIN,

629
00:36:26,977 --> 00:36:29,395
WE WOULDN'T BE HAVING
THIS CONVERSATION.

630
00:36:29,395 --> 00:36:31,857
YOU'D HAVE CUT ME LOOSE BY NOW.

631
00:36:31,857 --> 00:36:34,651
I'M NOT GONNA DO THAT, MALCOLM.

632
00:36:38,196 --> 00:36:40,157
WHEN WE TRIGGERED
THAT SUB-DETONATOR,

633
00:36:40,157 --> 00:36:42,283
WHY DIDN'T THE MINE
EXPLODE RIGHT AWAY?

634
00:36:43,827 --> 00:36:46,038
HOW MANY SECONDS WENT BY
BEFORE I REARMED IT?

635
00:36:46,038 --> 00:36:48,748
-SIR?
-HOW MANY SECONDS?

636
00:36:48,748 --> 00:36:51,209
I DON'T REMEMBER.

637
00:36:51,209 --> 00:36:53,170
10, MAYBE 12.

638
00:36:53,170 --> 00:36:54,880
ARCHER: IT FELT MORE LIKE 20.

639
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:58,175
10, 20 -- WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?

640
00:36:58,175 --> 00:37:00,760
ARCHER: IF IT HAD EXPLODED...

641
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:03,847
HOW BIG WOULD
THE YIELD HAVE BEEN?

642
00:37:05,223 --> 00:37:07,809
REED: JUDGING BY THE DAMAGE
THE FIRST MINE CAUSED,

643
00:37:07,809 --> 00:37:10,770
I'D GUESS ABOUT A QUARTER
OF A KILOTON.

644
00:37:10,770 --> 00:37:12,981
WHAT ARE YOU GETTING AT, SIR?

645
00:37:18,444 --> 00:37:20,405
ARCHER: HOW CLOSE IS YOUR TEAM
TO FINISHING?

646
00:37:20,405 --> 00:37:22,448
TUCKER: THEY'RE DOWN TO
THE LAST FEW COUPLINGS.

647
00:37:22,448 --> 00:37:23,783
WHAT'S GOING ON OUT THERE?

648
00:37:23,783 --> 00:37:26,327
ARCHER: WE'RE GONNA
DETACH THE PLATING.

649
00:37:27,829 --> 00:37:29,956
I'M SURE YOU DID EVERYTHING
YOU COULD, CAPTAIN --

650
00:37:29,956 --> 00:37:31,958
I'M GOING WITH HIM.

651
00:37:31,958 --> 00:37:33,626
COULD A SHUTTLEPOD HATCH
WITHSTAND

652
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:35,212
A QUARTER-KILOTON BLAST?

653
00:37:35,212 --> 00:37:36,838
DEPENDS HOW CLOSE IT WAS.

654
00:37:36,838 --> 00:37:38,965
20 METERS, MAYBE 25.

655
00:37:38,965 --> 00:37:41,009
YEAH, THEY'RE REINFORCED
WITH DURITANIUM ALLOY.

656
00:37:41,009 --> 00:37:42,677
THEY CAN TAKE A HELL
OF A BEATING.

657
00:37:42,677 --> 00:37:44,303
WHAT DO YOU GOT IN MIND?

658
00:37:44,303 --> 00:37:46,264
I NEED TWO SHUTTLEPOD HATCHES.

659
00:37:46,264 --> 00:37:48,266
HAVE THEM BROUGHT UP HERE
ON THE DOUBLE.

660
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:50,560
-SIR?
-ON THE DOUBLE.

661
00:37:54,313 --> 00:37:57,025
CAPTAIN, I ASSUME
THERE'S NO POINT

662
00:37:57,025 --> 00:37:59,069
IN MY QUESTIONING YOUR PLAN.

663
00:38:15,418 --> 00:38:17,336
BRIDGE TO CAPTAIN ARCHER.

664
00:38:17,336 --> 00:38:19,923
-GO AHEAD.
-We're ready.

665
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:23,051
SEE YOU SOON.

666
00:38:23,051 --> 00:38:25,762
HANG ON, FELLAS.

667
00:38:28,598 --> 00:38:30,642
[ WHIRRING ]

668
00:39:04,092 --> 00:39:05,677
600 METERS.

669
00:39:05,677 --> 00:39:07,512
TUCKER: ANOTHER HUNDRED
OUGHT TO DO IT.

670
00:39:07,512 --> 00:39:09,181
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

671
00:39:09,181 --> 00:39:11,224
SUBCOMMANDER.

672
00:39:13,101 --> 00:39:14,519
HAIL THEM.

673
00:39:16,104 --> 00:39:18,481
NO RESPONSE.

674
00:39:18,481 --> 00:39:20,859
[ ALARM BEEPS ]

675
00:39:20,859 --> 00:39:22,110
THEY'RE CHARGING WEAPONS!

676
00:39:22,110 --> 00:39:24,112
T'POL: POLARIZE
THE HULL PLATING.

677
00:39:24,112 --> 00:39:25,780
I'LL DO WHAT I CAN,
BUT KEEP IN MIND

678
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:27,157
WE'RE MISSING SOME OF IT.

679
00:39:31,328 --> 00:39:32,662
REED: IT'S REARMING!

680
00:39:37,209 --> 00:39:39,544
ARCHER: THAT'S IT. LET'S GO.

681
00:39:57,354 --> 00:39:59,397
NOW, MALCOLM!

682
00:40:09,157 --> 00:40:11,910
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> TO CAPTAIN ARCHER.

683
00:40:16,414 --> 00:40:18,499
T'POL: CAPTAIN, RESPOND.

684
00:40:21,419 --> 00:40:24,463
MAYBE THEIR TRANSMITTERS WERE
KNOCKED OUT IN THE BLAST.

685
00:40:24,463 --> 00:40:26,465
TRAVIS?

686
00:40:26,465 --> 00:40:28,426
I SEE THEM.

687
00:40:28,426 --> 00:40:31,429
BEARING 213 MARK 4.

688
00:40:31,429 --> 00:40:32,972
CLOSING IN.

689
00:40:32,972 --> 00:40:34,807
T'POL: OPEN THE DOORS
TO LAUNCH BAY 2.

690
00:40:34,807 --> 00:40:36,017
[ ALARM BEEPS ]

691
00:40:36,017 --> 00:40:37,269
THE ROMULANS
ARE LOCKING WEAPONS!

692
00:40:37,269 --> 00:40:39,938
-BRIDGE TO DR. PHLOX.
-Go ahead.

693
00:40:39,938 --> 00:40:42,065
MEET US OUTSIDE LAUNCH BAY 2.

694
00:40:42,065 --> 00:40:44,067
TUCKER: THEY'RE
TARGETING OUR ENGINES!

695
00:40:44,067 --> 00:40:47,195
100 METERS MORE.

696
00:40:47,195 --> 00:40:49,155
50.

697
00:40:49,155 --> 00:40:51,908
I'VE GOT THEM.
SEALING LAUNCH BAY DOORS.

698
00:40:51,908 --> 00:40:53,952
GO TO WARP, ENSIGN.

699
00:41:01,084 --> 00:41:03,128
[ PANTING ]

700
00:41:11,386 --> 00:41:12,971
YOU ALL RIGHT?

701
00:41:12,971 --> 00:41:15,390
UH-HUH, ALL THINGS
CONSIDERED.

702
00:41:15,390 --> 00:41:17,016
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

703
00:41:17,016 --> 00:41:19,018
IF I MAY SAY SO, SIR,

704
00:41:19,018 --> 00:41:22,688
YOUR STYLE OF COMMAND
DOES HAVE ITS ADVANTAGES.

705
00:41:23,773 --> 00:41:26,443
SO, HOW LONG WAS IT?

706
00:41:26,443 --> 00:41:28,069
[ GRUNTING ]

707
00:41:28,069 --> 00:41:31,072
I COUNTED 10 SECONDS.

708
00:41:31,072 --> 00:41:34,075
